I have been to the Peking Mandarin Restaurant on several occasions and have yet to have a bad experience. Every visit the staff and the cashier are always courteous, kind and  professional. On my most recent visit, my wife and I ordered the seafood soup and the sweet and spicy chicken along with some hot tea. We split the seafood soup and rightfully so because for one person you'd have to take the rest home.  The sweet and spicy wings that I ordered were bone in, but there is also the option of boneless. The wings were juicy and succulent while the sauce had a nice balance of sweet and spicy. So much so that I covered the white rice that came with the wings with the leftover sauce. We can't wait for our next visit and I would recommend the restaurant to any interested. Five Stars!!!!
